undergraduate programs at ccsre center for comparative studies in race and ethnicity skip to main content area about the center contact log in home fellowship programs undergraduate education research institute programs & institutes faculty development publications ccsre enews people ccsre undergraduate programs ccsre houses two interdepartmental undergraduate programs the program in african & african american studies aaas and the undergraduate program in comparative studies in race and ethnicity csre undergraduate programs at ccsre undergraduate programs at ccsre the program in african and african american studies aaas offers students the option of an interdisciplinary major or minor focusing on issues related to the african diaspora the program's director is arnetha f ball professor of education and the associate director is dr cheryl brown for more information about the program contact the aaas administrative assistant at 723 3782 additional information is also available at the aaas website the undergraduate program in comparative studies in race and ethnicity csre offers interdisciplinary honors for majors and non majors as well as majors and minors in four areas asian american studies chicana o studies comparative studies native american studies the csre program's director is jose david saldivar professor of comparative literature and the associate director is dr tania mitchell for more information about the program contact student services coordinator sarah gamino at 724 2088 or sgamino stanford edu 2010 stanford university the center for comparative studies in race and ethnicity stanford california 94305 650 723 2244 terms of use stay connected
